text:
AWS, And How BYJU's Has Grown With It
In this post, I’ll be discussing how AWS is helping BYJU’s with its business by providing them a number of different cloud services, about which I’ll be discussing further at a quite high level.
AWS, or Amazon Web Services, is a cloud service that was founded by the e-commerce giant Amazon in 2006. It was the first of its kind to provide Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), with the launch of AWS Elastic Compute Cloud in August 2006. Due to AWS being the first, and no other competitor existing in the market for the kind of service it provided, it took quite a few years before any AWS competitor arrived.
AWS Services used by BYJU's :-

Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2)

BYJU's website and mobile apps are being hosted on Amazon's EC2 instances. EC2 is a cloud service by AWS that is used to rent "virtual servers" on Amazon's data centers, which can be used to host our own applications, such as a website, or for even training ML models on some of the most powerful compute resources available in AWS.

Relational Database Service (RDS)

Amazon RDS is being used by BYJU's for their PostgreSQL database service, which is also their primary database service. The purpose of using RDS is to set up, operate, and scale a relational database in the cloud.
Redshift

Redshift
 as quoted by Amazon itself, 
"is the world's fastest cloud data warehouse". "But what is a data warehouse", you ask? In simple words, it's nothing but a large collection of business data, that is quite helpful for an organization in making decisions.

Implementing AWS has been a crucial step in the growth of BYJU's. The edtech giant is able to support more than 15 million users on its website and app, all due to the reliable and scalable cloud environment of AWS, which is able to scale on demand as their business keeps growing.
Ramachandran says,
We now have more than 15 million students using the BYJU’S mobile app, and we could not support that number without being on AWS.

You've been approaching Public Speaking wrongly. Here's why





Public speaking doesn't have to be a daunting task. 

Instead of seeing it as a necessary evil, consider it as a powerful tool to inspire, educate, and connect with your audience. 



Today! I’ll share with you a game-changing perspective that can transform the way you approach public speaking. 



1). Rather than fearing judgment or trying to impress the audience, focus on authenticity and connection..... Share your story, your passion, and your knowledge with genuine enthusiasm.



2). Another misconception is the need to be flawless. Imperfection make you human! Audiences appreciate vulnerability and will be more receptive to your message.



3). Practicing is vital, but it's not just about memorization. Instead, focus on understanding your content deeply, and let your passion guide you.



4). One common mistake is adopting a one-size-fits-all approach. Understand your audience's needs, interests, and pain points.  



5). Lastly, don't forget that public speaking is a skill, and like any skill, it improves with practice. Embrace every opportunity to speak, seek feedback, and grow from each experience. 



Change the narrative around public speaking! Embrace authenticity, value connection over perfection, and hone your skill through practice. 



The world is waiting to hear your voice, so go out there and rock that stage!🎤

💛”Positive self-talk isn't about believing you're perfect, it's about realizing that you're worth the effort of becoming your best self." - Natalie Norton

 💛MIRRORING and AFFIRMATIONS in the MIRROR are powerful self-improvement techniques that offer various benefits to our mental and emotional well-being. 

💛Here are some of the key reasons why these practices are important:

   ▪️Building Self-Awareness➖It fosters self-awareness, helping us recognize our emotions, thoughts, and reactions, which can be essential for our personal growth and development.

   ▪️Enhancing Self-Confidence➖Affirmations in the mirror reinforce positive self-beliefs, which, in turn, boost our self-confidence.

   ▪️Positive Self-Image➖Engaging with ourselves in the mirror through mirroring and affirmations encourages self-acceptance and self-love.

   ▪️Overcoming Negative Thought Patterns➖Both mirroring and affirmations interrupt our negative thought patterns that might be deeply ingrained. 

   ▪️Improved Nonverbal Communication➖Mirroring involves observing and refining nonverbal communication, such as our body language and facial expressions.This can be beneficial for those who wish to enhance their communication skills and social interactions.

   ▪️Empowerment➖it allows us to take control of our self-perception and actively work towards self-improvement and personal development.

   ▪️Stress Reduction➖Regularly taking a few moments to focus on positive self-affirmations can reduce our  stress and promote our emotional well-being.

   ▪️Mindfulness Practice➖This mindfulness aspect can help us become more grounded, centered, and connected to our emotions and experiences.

   ▪️Positive Impact on Mental Health➖Regularly practicing mirroring and affirmations can contribute to better mental health outcomes, as it encourages a positive mindset and a sense of self-empowerment.

 💛◼️For those with selective mutism, social anxiety or for ANY of US walking this earth, mirroring and affirmations in the mirror are practices that require consistency and patience. While they might feel awkward or uncomfortable at first, persisting with them can lead to significant improvements in self-confidence, self-compassion, and our overall well-being.

💠 Why we should not judge people by their appearance. ❓ 👇


🔶 True character, intelligence, kindness, and other valuable qualities cannot be assessed by appearance. 

🔷 Judging others solely based on appearances can lead to unfair assumptions and prejudices. 

🔺 When we refrain from judging based on appearances, we cultivate empathy.

🔻 By not judging others based on appearance, we set an example for personal growth and self-awareness.

🔹 When we don't judge others by their appearance, we create a space where people feel comfortable being themselves and expressing their true identity.

🔸 Empathy allows us to understand and connect with others on a deeper level, fostering compassion and understanding.

💠  It encourages us to examine our biases and work towards a more open-minded perspective.

✨ Me and Mic- A love story ✨

It's been over 3 months now, but I can't stop reminiscing about Renaissance 2023! 😊

Throwing back to the amazing days of Ren'23 - a fantastic mix of technology and culture that left a lasting impact on my college experience. From pulsating DJ nights to adrenaline-pumping competitions, it was an absolute rollercoaster of emotions.

I had the incredible opportunity to host the main stage event on Day 3, with an audience of over 4,500 people.🤩
It was an exceptional moment engaging the crowd, introducing talented performers, and witnessing Arjun Kanungo's mesmerizing performance, making the night truly unforgettable. 

For some, holding a microphone can be stressful , but for me, it's different. I feel confident and thoroughly enjoy the experience (Thanks to the continuous practice).

But that's not all; I also participated in short film making competition! 🎥 Crafting a narrative that resonated with the audience was an incredible journey of self-expression. And guess what? Won the cash prize 🎬

I would like to express my gratitude to the organizing team, Pranshu sir and Mohak ma'am for planning and executing this successful fest, also to all participants for creating lifelong memories.

Fiber is Your Friend! Here's Why You Need to Load Up 

Eating enough fiber is one of the most important things you can do for your health and wellbeing. Here's the deal on why you should aim high when it comes to your daily fiber intake:

Fiber aids digestion and keeps things moving smoothly through your system. It adds bulk to stool and prevents constipation. Getting enough fiber also reduces your risk for digestive disorders like diverticulitis.  

Fiber helps control blood sugar by slowing the rate that sugar enters your bloodstream after a meal. This makes it especially beneficial for those with diabetes or insulin resistance. 

It lowers LDL (bad) cholesterol by binding to cholesterol and removing it from your body before it can clog your arteries. This supports better heart health.

Eating more fiber-rich foods can help you feel full on fewer calories, aiding weight control and loss. The bulk fills you up and suppresses appetite.

Higher fiber intake is associated with a reduced risk for some cancers, stroke, and heart disease. It also helps control blood pressure.

Aim for 25-30 grams per day from fruits, vegetables, beans, lentils, nuts, seeds and whole grains. Stay hydrated to keep fiber moving smoothly through your system.
